## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests. 0 real verifications.** This is a textbook **coverage-touching** suite — every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (giving you that 95% coverage number), but almost nothing is actually verified. Bugs sail through because these tests cannot fail unless the production code throws an unhandled exception.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 6 |
| High | 1 |
| Medium | 2 |
| Low | 1 |

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (systemic — entire test class)

The class methodically calls every public method on `ProductCatalog` with no meaningful assertions. This is the single root cause of your "95% coverage, still finding bugs" problem.

**Tests with zero assertions (4 of 10):**

| Line | Method | What it misses |
|------|--------|---------------|
| 17 | `AddProduct_Works` | Never checks the product was actually stored |
| 33 | `UpdatePrice_Works` | Never checks the price actually changed |
| 39 | `RemoveProduct_Works` | Never checks the product was actually removed |
| 68 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | Never checks any prices were reduced |
| 87 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` | Never checks any products were imported |

**Fix — `AddProduct_Works` (line 17):**
```csharp
// BEFORE — passes even if AddProduct silently no-ops
var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
_catalog.AddProduct(product);

// AFTER — verifies the product is retrievable with correct data
var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(stored);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored.Price);
```

**Fix — `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 33):**
```csharp
// BEFORE — calls UpdatePrice, never checks the new price
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

// AFTER — verifies the price actually changed
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

**Fix — `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 39):**
```csharp
// BEFORE
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

